Chrystal Herne https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chrystal_Herne 0 Katherine Chrystal Herne (June 16, 1883 – September 19, 1950) was an American stage actress. She was the daughter of actor/playwright, James A. Herne, and the younger sister of actress and Hollywood talent scout, Julie Herne. Her stage credits include creating the title role in the original Broadway production of George Kelly's Pulitzer Prize winning play, Craig's Wife (1925).
